02:07:56,190 --> 02:08:00,690
She booked a table for eight o'clock and then
went into the shop.

2096
02:08:00,690 --> 02:08:05,110
If Mrs Lennox had somehow managed to learn
anything about her and Tristan, she wanted

2097
02:08:05,110 --> 02:08:08,760
to give her the chance to say it directly
to her face.

2098
02:08:08,760 --> 02:08:11,659
But fortunately nothing was said.

2099
02:08:11,659 --> 02:08:15,200
When she got back, Stephen was waiting for
her.

2100
02:08:15,200 --> 02:08:20,170
'You rushed out so quickly you didn't give
me time to tell you my news!' he said, smiling

2101
02:08:20,170 --> 02:08:21,170
happily.

2102
02:08:21,170 --> 02:08:26,030
'I rang Charlie to ask him about the chances
of my having to leave the new company.

2103
02:08:26,030 --> 02:08:29,800
He thought I was worried and tried to say
nice things.

2104
02:08:29,800 --> 02:08:33,389
But when I told him I wanted to leave, he
laughed.'

2105
02:08:33,389 --> 02:08:34,699
'Why?'

2106
02:08:34,699 --> 02:08:35,969
asked Anna.

2107
02:08:35,969 --> 02:08:40,260
'Because apparently the new managing director
was just about to tell me that I had lost

2108
02:08:40,260 --> 02:08:44,290
my job, and he was not looking forward to
saying it,' said Stephen.

2109
02:08:44,290 --> 02:08:46,170
'When will this happen?'

2110
02:08:46,170 --> 02:08:48,030
'In a couple of months!'

2111
02:08:48,030 --> 02:08:49,380
Stephen replied happily.

2112
02:08:49,380 --> 02:08:54,469
'I'll be free of Jardine's - and I'll have
a "thank you and goodbye" present of a year's

2113
02:08:54,469 --> 02:08:55,840
salary.

2114
02:08:55,840 --> 02:08:57,440
Not bad, eh?

2115
02:08:57,440 --> 02:09:00,610
Somebody, somewhere is taking care of us,
don't you think?

2116
02:09:00,610 --> 02:09:03,290
This is exactly what I wanted.'

2117
02:09:03,290 --> 02:09:08,489
'Stephen, that's great - if it's really what
you want.'

2118
02:09:08,489 --> 02:09:10,530
'It is.

2119
02:09:10,530 --> 02:09:13,639
Anna, are you having second thoughts?'

2120
02:09:13,639 --> 02:09:19,170
'No, not at all,' she replied quickly.

2121
02:09:19,170 --> 02:09:23,280
Stephen took hold of her as she walked past
his chair on the way upstairs.

2122
02:09:23,280 --> 02:09:27,430
She fell backwards onto him and he kissed
the back of her neck.

2123
02:09:27,430 --> 02:09:30,239
'Mmm... salt and fish!

2124
02:09:30,239 --> 02:09:31,909
You smell wonderful!'

2125
02:09:31,909 --> 02:09:34,270
'I need a shower.'

2126
02:09:34,270 --> 02:09:38,119
She got up and kissed him on the nose.

2127
02:09:38,119 --> 02:09:40,550
The shower helped.

2128
02:09:40,550 --> 02:09:43,000
'Everything's working out well for him,' she
thought.

2129
02:09:43,000 --> 02:09:46,760
'There's no way I can suddenly change my mind
about living here.

2130
02:09:46,760 --> 02:09:49,580
God, I feel awful.

2131
02:09:49,580 --> 02:09:52,809
He would be so hurt if he ever found out.

2132
02:09:52,809 --> 02:09:54,440
I'm a fool!

2133
02:09:54,440 --> 02:09:55,530
I'm confused!

2134
02:09:55,530 --> 02:10:00,000
I don't know what to think anymore.'

2135
02:10:00,000 --> 02:10:02,330
She dried herself roughly.

2136
02:10:02,330 --> 02:10:06,909
The main thing now was to get through the
next few hours without a disaster.

2137
02:10:06,909 --> 02:10:09,639
Real thinking would come later.

2138
02:10:09,639 --> 02:10:11,849
She found Stephen in the front garden.

2139
02:10:11,849 --> 02:10:14,040
'Better?' he said.

2140
02:10:14,040 --> 02:10:16,139
'Yes, much.'

2141
02:10:16,139 --> 02:10:19,639
'Something's changed,' he said looking around.

2142
02:10:19,639 --> 02:10:21,719
'What do you mean?'

2143
02:10:21,719 --> 02:10:23,170
she asked quickly.

2144
02:10:23,170 --> 02:10:25,909
'The air smells different.

2145
02:10:25,909 --> 02:10:29,480
I think there is going to be a storm, after
all.'

2146
02:10:29,480 --> 02:10:35,250
'Good,' she said before realizing what she
was saying.

2147
02:10:35,250 --> 02:10:39,910
As they went up the hill to Philpots, they
could hear thunder in the distance and the

2148
02:10:39,910 --> 02:10:43,320
first whisper of wind cooled their faces.

2149
02:10:43,320 --> 02:10:48,800
Over dinner, Stephen was full of plans - what
he was going to do, when they'd be able to

2150
02:10:48,800 --> 02:10:55,050
come back down, how they'd have to buy another
car - or maybe he'd get a motorbike.

2151
02:10:55,050 --> 02:10:58,849
Anna listened, smiled and said very little.

2152
02:10:58,849 --> 02:11:05,010
Their dinner was excellent and the wine helped
Anna to relax more.

2153
02:11:05,010 --> 02:11:09,460
When they left the restaurant, the wind had
got stronger and big drops of rain were hitting

2154
02:11:09,460 --> 02:11:11,520
the ground, hard.

2155
02:11:11,520 --> 02:11:14,790
The storm was coming in from the west.

2156
02:11:14,790 --> 02:11:18,449
Skellig was suddenly lit up by a flash of
lightning.

2157
02:11:18,449 --> 02:11:23,059
Stephen put his sweater over his head and
they both ran down the street.

2158
02:11:23,059 --> 02:11:24,329
Then they saw Tristan.

2159
02:11:24,329 --> 02:11:27,070
'Oh, hi!' said Tristan.

2160
02:11:27,070 --> 02:11:31,679
'I was just going to make sure the boat was
tied up properly.'

2161
02:11:31,679 --> 02:11:35,270
Another flash of lightning showed the white
tops of the waves in the harbour.

2162
02:11:35,270 --> 02:11:41,210
'Want some help?' asked Stephen, but Tristan
was already moving away.

2163
02:11:41,210 --> 02:11:43,210
The air was electric.

2164
02:11:43,210 --> 02:11:46,650
'Come on, Stephen,' said Anna running down
the street.

2165
02:11:46,650 --> 02:11:51,280
'Let's get home before it gets any worse.'

2166
02:11:51,280 --> 02:11:54,680
As they reached the cottage, there was a huge
crash of thunder.

2167
02:11:54,680 --> 02:11:57,980
They stood in the doorway and watched.

2168
02:11:57,980 --> 02:12:02,260
With each flash of lightning, the sky was
lit up and they could see ghostly figures

2169
02:12:02,260 --> 02:12:05,260
in the harbour, checking boat ropes.

2170
02:12:05,260 --> 02:12:08,199
'The water's high tonight,' said Stephen.

2171
02:12:08,199 --> 02:12:14,360
'We've never seen it so high - no wonder Tristan
was worried.'

2172
02:12:14,360 --> 02:12:16,829
Stephen and Anna went upstairs to bed.

2173
02:12:16,829 --> 02:12:20,460
But the storm was so wild and beautiful.

2174
02:12:20,460 --> 02:12:26,949
Anna stood at the bedroom window with Stephen
behind her, his arms holding her close.

2175
02:12:26,949 --> 02:12:30,139
'Next week'll be strange without you here,'
he said.

2176
02:12:30,139 --> 02:12:32,429
'No, it won't.

2177
02:12:32,429 --> 02:12:36,540
You'll be so busy arranging things you won't
have time to notice.

2178
02:12:36,540 --> 02:12:41,440
In any case, it'll give you a chance to get
used to it,' replied Anna.

2179
02:12:41,440 --> 02:12:43,449
'In what way?'

2180
02:12:43,449 --> 02:12:48,020
'Well, I might not be able to move down here
as soon as you.

2181
02:12:48,020 --> 02:12:51,200
I don't know about my job and things yet,
do I?

2182
02:12:51,200 --> 02:12:55,650
You might have to spend a bit of time here
alone,' said Anna, and added quickly, 'before

2183
02:12:55,650 --> 02:12:57,210
I can join you.'

2184
02:12:57,210 --> 02:12:58,210
'Oh.

2185
02:12:58,210 --> 02:13:01,159
We'll have to talk about that next weekend.

2186
02:13:01,159 --> 02:13:03,230
I don't want to come back without you.

2187
02:13:03,230 --> 02:13:08,020
I want to start this together,' and he kissed
the back of her neck.

2188
02:13:08,020 --> 02:13:11,750
They went to bed and reached for each other.

2189
02:13:11,750 --> 02:13:16,750
His body was usually so familiar and lovely
but tonight she felt uncomfortable with his

2190
02:13:16,750 --> 02:13:23,590
body beside her and her dreams that night
were full of disturbing pictures.

2191
02:13:23,590 --> 02:13:28,429
In the morning, it took a long time to wake
from her deep sleep - the dreams were still

2192
02:13:28,429 --> 02:13:31,329
pulling her back down.

2193
02:13:31,329 --> 02:13:35,840
Stephen wasn't there, so she slowly got out
of bed and walked to the window.

2194
02:13:35,840 --> 02:13:38,550
The scene outside was much changed.

2195
02:13:38,550 --> 02:13:41,420
The storm had passed but the sky was grey.

2196
02:13:41,420 --> 02:13:47,909
Rain had washed away all the summer's dirt
and the streets looked fresh.

2197
02:13:47,909 --> 02:13:54,010
She looked down at the harbour - Wave Dancer
was still there, good - but she noticed three

2198
02:13:54,010 --> 02:13:57,760
other boats on the beach, on their sides.

2199
02:13:57,760 --> 02:14:03,160
Several people were down there, standing around,
including Stephen and Tristan.

2200
02:14:03,160 --> 02:14:06,420
She turned away from the window.

2201
02:14:06,420 --> 02:14:10,079
When Stephen came back, she was ready to leave.

2202
02:14:10,079 --> 02:14:17,659
She walked around the cottage-saying goodbye
to it, wondering when - and if - she'd return.

2203
02:14:17,659 --> 02:14:21,280
Her feelings this morning matched the sky.

2204
02:14:21,280 --> 02:14:25,309
Stephen thought she was unhappy because she
was going back to London, and she let him

2205
02:14:25,309 --> 02:14:26,309
think that.

2206
02:14:26,309 --> 02:14:31,710
They said a rather sad goodbye at Kingham
station.

2207
02:14:31,710 --> 02:14:37,010
She stood at the carriage window, waving to
Stephen until he disappeared.

2208
02:14:37,010 --> 02:14:42,600
Then she suddenly started to cry.

2209
02:14:42,600 --> 02:14:44,550
CHAPTER SIXTEEN

2210
02:14:44,550 --> 02:14:48,579
The end of the affair

2211
02:14:48,579 --> 02:14:53,810
Back in London, Anna tried to get herself
back into her normal routine.

2212
02:14:53,810 --> 02:14:59,070
She was busy at the hospital, and that kept
her mind fully occupied.

2213
02:14:59,070 --> 02:15:03,969
Everybody kept telling her how well she looked,
and younger, too, and that the seaside was

2214
02:15:03,969 --> 02:15:06,940
obviously good for her.

2215
02:15:06,940 --> 02:15:11,050
The routine of her familiar life helped her
to calm down.

2216
02:15:11,050 --> 02:15:17,580
In the evenings, in the flat alone, she thought
about Polreath and Tristan and Stephen, and

2217
02:15:17,580 --> 02:15:23,659
she gradually began to realise that what had
happened was no more than a holiday love affair.

2218
02:15:23,659 --> 02:15:29,530
A mixture of lots of different things had
let it happen - Stephen's work crisis, her

2219
02:15:29,530 --> 02:15:34,460
need for some sort of change, the fact that
Tristan was very attractive and was attracted

2220
02:15:34,460 --> 02:15:40,590
to her, and the fact that he was so open and
easy to talk to - unlike Stephen recently

2221
02:15:40,590 --> 02:15:45,889
- and of course the magic of the sun and the
sea.

2222
02:15:45,889 --> 02:15:49,849
But understanding it didn't make her feel
any better.

2223
02:15:49,849 --> 02:15:54,440
She felt guilty that she had started something
with Tristan that she knew now she couldn't

2224
02:15:54,440 --> 02:15:55,580
continue.

2225
02:15:55,580 --> 02:16:00,540
She had a horrible feeling, however, that
it was different for Tristan - but then he

2226
02:16:00,540 --> 02:16:04,139
wasn't married; he had less to lose.

2227
02:16:04,139 --> 02:16:06,270
And she was right.

2228
02:16:06,270 --> 02:16:09,480
Tristan couldn't get Anna out of his mind.

2229
02:16:09,480 --> 02:16:12,610
The only time he felt calm was when he went
out fishing.

2230
02:16:12,610 --> 02:16:18,210
And as for talking to Stephen - well, it was
getting more and more difficult.

2231
02:16:18,210 --> 02:16:24,060
Stephen, however, wanted to get on with the
business of buying Dolphin Cottage.

2232
02:16:24,060 --> 02:16:28,739
They had agreed on the sale price, and he
wanted to pay Tristan the deposit before he

2233
02:16:28,739 --> 02:16:32,030
went back to London at the weekend.

2234
02:16:32,030 --> 02:16:36,910
So early on Wednesday morning, he went down
to the harbour and found Tristan busy on his

2235
02:16:36,910 --> 02:16:37,910
boat.

2236
02:16:37,910 --> 02:16:40,640
'Morning, Tristan,' he said.

2237
02:16:40,640 --> 02:16:43,210
'Didn't see you yesterday.

2238
02:16:43,210 --> 02:16:44,490
Everything OK?'

2239
02:16:44,490 --> 02:16:49,760
'Yes, fine thanks,' Tristan replied as he
untied the ropes that held Wave Dancer to

2240
02:16:49,760 --> 02:16:51,610
the harbour wall.

2241
02:16:51,610 --> 02:16:57,189
'I'm just going to pick up the lobster pots
I put down yesterday, behind Skellig.'

2242
02:16:57,189 --> 02:16:58,200
'Right.

2243
02:16:58,200 --> 02:17:00,960
Look, can we meet tomorrow evening?

2244
02:17:00,960 --> 02:17:04,019
I should have the cheque by then,' said Stephen.

2245
02:17:04,019 --> 02:17:09,700
'In the Fisherman's about seven?' said Tristan
turning Wave Dancer away from the harbour

2246
02:17:09,700 --> 02:17:10,700
wall.

2247
02:17:10,700 --> 02:17:16,760
'Sorry, Stephen, can't stop to talk now, I've
got a lot to do.'

2248
02:17:16,760 --> 02:17:22,310
On Thursday morning, Anna woke up with a clear
head - as soon as she opened her eyes, she

2249
02:17:22,310 --> 02:17:25,130
knew that they couldn't buy Dolphin Cottage.

2250
02:17:25,130 --> 02:17:27,439
They couldn't live in Polreath.

2251
02:17:27,439 --> 02:17:33,019
She knew that seeing Tristan every day would
be a constant reminder and, if she was honest,

2252
02:17:33,019 --> 02:17:37,219
she was afraid that what had happened once
could happen again.

2253
02:17:37,219 --> 02:17:40,639
Was she really strong enough to cut the relationship?

2254
02:17:40,639 --> 02:17:43,660
Tristan was lovely - too lovely to hurt any
more.

2255
02:17:43,660 --> 02:17:48,430
Surely, it was better to end it all now while
she still had the choice.

2256
02:17:48,430 --> 02:17:50,099
Stephen need never know.

2257
02:17:50,099 --> 02:17:54,820
Anna stood in the shower, letting the water
run over her face.

2258
02:17:54,820 --> 02:17:58,120
'Oh Stephen, I'm sorry.

2259
02:17:58,120 --> 02:18:00,840
You'd never trust me again if you found out,
would you?'

2260
02:18:00,840 --> 02:18:02,750
Anna thought.

2261
02:18:02,750 --> 02:18:07,320
She realised she didn't want to lose him and
the life they had together.

2262
02:18:07,320 --> 02:18:12,890
True, some of the early excitement had disappeared
over the ten years of their married life,

2263
02:18:12,890 --> 02:18:17,920
and he could be difficult to live with but
she knew him so well.

2264
02:18:17,920 --> 02:18:22,820
She knew what he liked to eat, she knew the
way he combed his hair, she knew what he would

2265
02:18:22,820 --> 02:18:24,649
think about a programme on TV.

2266
02:18:24,649 --> 02:18:27,850
He was part of her.

2267
02:18:27,850 --> 02:18:32,290
The first thing she had to do was stop Stephen
buying Dolphin Cottage tonight.

2268
02:18:32,290 --> 02:18:38,590
He was going to be very confused about why
she had changed her mind and horribly disappointed.

2269
02:18:38,590 --> 02:18:40,590
And he'd have to find a new job somewhere.

2270
02:18:40,590 --> 02:18:41,740
Oh God!

2271
02:18:41,740 --> 02:18:48,300
How was she going to explain her reasons - maybe
she could introduce the idea of moving out

2272
02:18:48,300 --> 02:18:52,870
of London but not going quite so far as Cornwall.

2273
02:18:52,870 --> 02:18:57,380
It was true she had been thinking about the
things she would miss when they moved - her

2274
02:18:57,380 --> 02:18:59,979
friends, the fun of living in the capital
city.

2275
02:18:59,979 --> 02:19:01,700
What about Brighton!

2276
02:19:01,700 --> 02:19:07,250
Lots of London people moved to Brighton, and
she and Stephen had always enjoyed the weekends

2277
02:19:07,250 --> 02:19:10,300
they had spent there.

2278
02:19:10,300 --> 02:19:13,080
Just as she was walking through to the kitchen,
the phone rang.

2279
02:19:13,080 --> 02:19:15,550
It made her jump.

2280
02:19:15,550 --> 02:19:18,710
'Stephen, or Mum,' she thought.

2281
02:19:18,710 --> 02:19:22,550
'They're the only people who'd phone so early
in the morning.

2282
02:19:22,550 --> 02:19:25,559
Or maybe it's Tristan.'

2283
02:19:25,559 --> 02:19:29,250
Whoever it was, she wasn't ready to speak.

2284
02:19:29,250 --> 02:19:32,010
She picked it up nervously.

2285
02:19:32,010 --> 02:19:34,319
It was Stephen.

2286
02:19:34,319 --> 02:19:37,189
'Anna, I've just seen Tristan.

2287
02:19:37,189 --> 02:19:39,719
He's just told me something.

2288
02:19:39,719 --> 02:19:42,719
We've got to talk.'

2289
02:19:42,719 --> 02:20:16,109
Anna's heart froze.

